Interface Summary
Entity<ID> Entity - from wikipedia: An object that is not defined by its attributes, but rather by a thread of continuity and its identity.
EntityBuilder<B extends EntityBuilder<?,?>,E extends Entity<?>> By convention, implementations should have two constructors: Default constructor for creating an immutable Entity from scratch Copy constructor which creates an immutable Entity by copying the prototype For more information about the builder pattern can be found here.
